openvr
------------------------------------------
OpenVR is an API and runtime that allows access to VR hardware from multiple
vendors without requiring that applications have specific knowledge of the
hardware they are targeting. This repository is an SDK that contains the API
and samples. The runtime is under SteamVR in Tools on Steam.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.9.0-3
  libgcc1-6.4.0-4
  libopenvr_api-devel-1.0.11-1bl1
  libopenvr_api1.0.0-1.0.11-1bl1
  libstdc++6-6.4.0-4
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.25.0-1
  gcc-core-6.4.0-4
  gcc-g++-6.4.0-4
  lua-5.2.4-1
  make-4.2.1-2
  python-2.7.14-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/ValveSoftware/openvr

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/ValveSoftware/openvr/archive/v1.0.11.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack openvr-1.0.11-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./openvr-1.0.11-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/openvr-1.0.11-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/openvr-1.0.11-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libopenvr_api1.0.0-1.0.11-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libopenvr_api-devel-1.0.11-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(openvr)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/openvr.README
  /usr/share/doc/openvr/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/openvr/README.md

(libopenvr_api1.0.0)
  /usr/bin/cygopenvr_api-1.0.0.dll

(libopenvr_api-devel)
  /usr/include/openvr/openvr.h
  /usr/include/openvr/openvr_capi.h
  /usr/include/openvr/openvr_driver.h
  /usr/lib/libopenvr_api.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/openvr.pc

